Rates for each reaction channel r_i calculated from current state.\n        2. The timestep tau is chosen randomly from an exponential distribution P ~ e^(-W tau).\n        3. A single reaction occurs with probablity proportional to its fractional rate constant r_i/W.\n        4. The state is updated to reflect this reaction occuring and time is propagated forward by tau\n\n        Stops if population becomes too small.\n\n\n        Parameters\n        ----------\n        contactMatrix: python function(t)\n             The social contact matrix C_{ij} denotes the\n             average number of contacts made per day by an\n             individual in class i with an individual in class j\n        Tf: float\n            Final time of integrator\n        Nf: Int\n            Number of time points to evaluate.\n\n\n        Returns\n        -------\n        t_arr : np.array(Nf,)\n            Array of time points at which the integrator was evaluated.\n        out_arr : np.array\n            Output path from integrator.\n        ";

static char __pyx_doc_6pyross_10stochastic_22stochastic_integration_6simulate_tau_leaping[] = "\n        Tau leaping algorithm for producing stochastically correct trajectories\n        Based on Cao et al (2006):\n        https://doi.org/10.1063/1.2159468\n        This method can run much faster than the Gillespie algorithm\n\n        1. Rates for each reaction channel r_i calculated from current state.\n        2. Timestep tau chosen such that \\Delta r_i < epsilon \\Sum r_i\n        3. Number of reactions that occur in channel i ~Poisson(r_i tau)\n        4. Update state by this amount\n\n        Parameters\n        ----------\n        contactMatrix: python function(t)\n             The social contact matrix C_{ij} denotes the\n             average number of contacts made per day by an\n             individual in class i with an individual in class j\n        Tf: float\n            Final time of integrator\n        Nf: Int\n            Number of time points to evaluate.\n        nc: optional\n            The default is 30\n        epsilon: float, optional\n            The acceptable relative change of the rates during each\n            tau-leaping step, as defined in Cao et al. The default is 0.03\n        tau_update_frequency: optional\n\n\n        Returns\n        -------\n        t_arr : np.array(Nf,)\n            Array of time points at which the integrator was evaluated.\n        out_arr : np.array\n            Output path from integrator.\n        ";

 0671:                           int nc = 30, double epsilon = 0.03,
 0672:                           int tau_update_frequency = 1):
 0673:         """
 0674:         Tau leaping algorithm for producing stochastically correct trajectories
 0675:         Based on Cao et al (2006):
 0676:         https://doi.org/10.1063/1.2159468
 0677:         This method can run much faster than the Gillespie algorithm
 0678: 
 0679:         1. Rates for each reaction channel r_i calculated from current state.
 0680:         2. Timestep tau chosen such that \Delta r_i < epsilon \Sum r_i
 0681:         3. Number of reactions that occur in channel i ~Poisson(r_i tau)
 0682:         4. Update state by this amount
 0683: 
 0684:         Parameters
 0685:         ----------
 0686:         contactMatrix: python function(t)
 0687:              The social contact matrix C_{ij} denotes the
 0688:              average number of contacts made per day by an
 0689:              individual in class i with an individual in class j
 0690:         Tf: float
 0691:             Final time of integrator
 0692:         Nf: Int
 0693:             Number of time points to evaluate.
 0694:         nc: optional
 0695:             The default is 30
 0696:         epsilon: float, optional
 0697:             The acceptable relative change of the rates during each
 0698:             tau-leaping step, as defined in Cao et al. The default is 0.03
 0699:         tau_update_frequency: optional
 0700: 
 0701: 
 0702:         Returns
 0703:         -------
 0704:         t_arr : np.array(Nf,)

 0706:         out_arr : np.array
 0707:             Output path from integrator.

 2820:     """
 2821:     Generic user-defined epidemic model.
 2822: 
 2823:     ...
 2824: 
 2825:     Parameters
 2826:     ----------
 2827:     model_spec: dict
 2828:         A dictionary specifying the model. See `Examples`.
 2829:     parameters: dict
 2830:         A dictionary containing the model parameters.
 2831:         All parameters can be float if not age-dependent, and np.array(M,) if age-dependent.
 2832:         An optional element with the key 'seed' may be supplied as a seed for the 
 2833:         pseudo-random number generator.
 2834:     M: int
 2835:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 2836:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 2837:     Ni: np.array(3*M, )
 2838:         Initial number in each compartment and class
 2839:     time_dep_param_mapping: python function, optional
 2840:         A user-defined function that takes a dictionary of time-independent parameters 
 2841:         and time as an argument, and returns a dictionary of the parameters of model_spec.
 2842:         Default: Identical mapping of the dictionary at all times.
 2843: 
 2844:     Examples
 2845:     --------
 2846:     An example of model_spec and parameters for SIR class with a constant influx
 2847: 
 2848:     >>> model_spec = {
 2849:             "classes" : ["S", "I"],
 2850:             "S" : {
 2851:                 "constant"  : [ ["k"] ],
 2852:                 "infection" : [ ["I", "S", "-beta"] ]
 2853:             },
 2854:             "I" : {
 2855:                 "linear"    : [ ["I", "-gamma"] ],
 2856:                 "infection" : [ ["I", "S", "beta"] ]
 2857:             }
 2858:         }
 2859:     >>> parameters = {
 2860:             'beta': 0.1,

 3304:     """
 3305:     This is a slightly more specific version of the class `Model`. 
 3306: 
 3307:     `Spp` is still supported for backward compatibility. 
 3308: 
 3309:     `Model` class is recommended over `Spp` for new users. 
 3310: 
 3311:     The `Spp` class works like `Model` but infection terms use a single class `S` 
 3312: 
 3313:     ...
 3314: 
 3315:     Parameters
 3316:     ----------
 3317:     model_spec: dict
 3318:         A dictionary specifying the model. See `Examples`.
 3319:     parameters: dict
 3320:         A dictionary containing the model parameters.
 3321:         All parameters can be float if not age-dependent, and np.array(M,) if age-dependent.
 3322:         An optional element with the key 'seed' may be supplied as a seed for the 
 3323:         pseudo-random number generator.
 3324:     M: int
 3325:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 3326:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 3327:     Ni: np.array(3*M, )
 3328:         Initial number in each compartment and class
 3329:     time_dep_param_mapping: python function, optional
 3330:         A user-defined function that takes a dictionary of 
 3331:         time-independent parameters and time as an argument, and 
 3332:         returns a dictionary of the parameters of model_spec.
 3333:         Default: Identical mapping of the dictionary at all times.
 3334: 
 3335:     Examples
 3336:     --------
 3337:     An example of model_spec and parameters for SIR class with a constant influx
 3338: 
 3339:     >>> model_spec = {
 3340:             "classes" : ["S", "I"],
 3341:             "S" : {
 3342:                 "constant"  : [ ["k"] ],
 3343:                 "infection" : [ ["I", "-beta"] ]
 3344:             },
 3345:             "I" : {
 3346:                 "linear"    : [ ["I", "-gamma"] ],
 3347:                 "infection" : [ ["I", "beta"] ]
 3348:             }
 3349:         }
 3350:     >>> parameters = {
 3351:             'beta': 0.1,
 3352:             'gamma': 0.1,
 3353:             'seed': 1234,
 3354:             'k': 1,
 3355:         }
 3356:     """
 3357:

 3367:     """User-defined epidemic model with quarantine stage.
 3368: 
 3369:     This is a slightly more specific version of the class `Model`. 
 3370: 
 3371:     `SppQ` is still supported for backward compatibility. 
 3372: 
 3373:     `Model` class is recommended over `SppQ` for new users. 
 3374: 
 3375:     To initialise the SppQ model,
 3376: 
 3377:     ...
 3378: 
 3379:     Parameters
 3380:     ----------
 3381:     model_spec: dict
 3382:         A dictionary specifying the model. See `Examples`.
 3383:     parameters: dict
 3384:         A dictionary containing the model parameters.
 3385:         All parameters can be float if not age-dependent, and np.array(M,) if age-dependent.
 3386:         An optional element with the key 'seed' may be supplied as a seed for the 
 3387:         pseudo-random number generator.
 3388:     M: int
 3389:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 3390:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 3391:     Ni: np.array(3*M, )
 3392:         Initial number in each compartment and class
 3393:     time_dep_param_mapping: python function, optional
 3394:         A user-defined function that takes a dictionary of time-independent parameters and time as an argument, and returns a dictionary of the parameters of model_spec.
 3395:         Default: Identical mapping of the dictionary at all times.
 3396: 
 3397:     Examples
 3398:     --------
 3399:     An example of model_spec and parameters for SIR class with random testing (without false positives/negatives) and quarantine
 3400: 
 3401:     >>> model_spec = {
 3402:             "classes" : ["S", "I"],
 3403:             "S" : {
 3404:                 "infection" : [ ["I", "-beta"] ]
 3405:             },
 3406:             "I" : {
 3407:                 "linear"    : [ ["I", "-gamma"] ],
 3408:                 "infection" : [ ["I", "beta"] ]
 3409:             },
 3410:             "test_pos"  : [ "p_falsepos", "p_truepos", "p_falsepos"] ,
 3411:             "test_freq" : [ "tf", "tf", "tf"]
 3412:         }
 3413:     >>> parameters = {
 3414:             'beta': 0.1,
 3415:             'gamma': 0.1,
 3416:             'seed': 1234,
 3417:             'p_falsepos': 0,
 3418:             'p_truepos': 1,
 3419:             'tf': 1
 3420:         }
 3421:     """
